'''Orleans-Essex Visiting Nurses Association and Hospice''', also known as '''Orleans-Essex VNA''', is a not-for-profit [[home care]] and [[hospice]] agency, which has served [[Orleans County, Vermont]] and [[Essex County, Vermont]] since its inception in 1969. The agency is certified by both [[Medicare (United States)|Medicare]] and [[Medicaid]]. 

The organization provides a variety of services that include nursing, personal care, physical therapy, occupational therapy, speech therapy,  nutritional guidance, home health care, pediatric care, case management and medical social work services.<ref>[http://www.northcountryschools.org/education/components/scrapbook/default.php?sectiondetailid=201&PHPSESSID=24ccee0722dd56ce25ac4beb53ae08bb]</ref>

==History==
Nancy Warner was hired in 1969 to lead the VNA. She still led it in 2009. The original budget was $25,000.<ref name="c090128">{{cite book | author = Starr, Tena |title = Orleans-Essex VNA celebrates 40 years | publisher = the Chronicle | date = January 28, 2009}}</ref>

In 2009, it employed 100 people. It made 4,000 home visits monthly to 300 people.<ref name="c090128"/>

